Product Name
ScrumPilot ‚Äî Your AI Scrum Assistant for GitLab
‚∏ª
1. Objective
During daily stand-ups or sprint review meetings, a lot of time is spent updating JIRA/GitLab boards manually after verbal discussions. ScrumPilot automates this by:
	‚Ä¢	Listening to team conversations during Scrum calls.
	‚Ä¢	Understanding who‚Äôs working on which issue.
	‚Ä¢	Updating issue statuses and adding comments automatically on GitLab.
This saves time, increases accuracy, and ensures the issue board always reflects reality.
‚∏ª
2. Problem Statement
Teams often:
	‚Ä¢	Forget to update issue statuses after daily calls.
	‚Ä¢	Spend unnecessary time on manual board management.
	‚Ä¢	Lose track of recent updates discussed verbally.
	‚Ä¢	Lack automated, structured logs of progress mentioned in meetings.
‚∏ª
3. Solution Overview
ScrumPilot will:
	‚Ä¢	Join the daily meeting (Google Meet, Zoom, or Microsoft Teams).
	‚Ä¢	Use speech-to-text + speaker diarization to identify who said what.
	‚Ä¢	Parse the spoken update (e.g., ‚ÄúI‚Äôve completed the backend API for ticket #123‚Äù) using NLP.
	‚Ä¢	Automatically:
	‚Ä¢	Change the ticket status on GitLab (e.g., from ‚ÄúIn Progress‚Äù ‚Üí ‚ÄúDone‚Äù).
	‚Ä¢	Add a summary comment under that issue (‚ÄúUpdate from Aman: Completed backend API.‚Äù)
	‚Ä¢	Optionally, tag the user who gave the update.
‚∏ª
4. Target Users
	‚Ä¢	Agile development teams using GitLab issue boards.
	‚Ä¢	Scrum Masters and Product Managers.
	‚Ä¢	Remote/distributed teams who rely on daily sync meetings.
‚∏ª
5. User Stories
